To prove the `map_smul'` field, we need to show that the integral of `f` against the measure `E_{a, x, c • y}` is `c` times the integral against `E_{a, x, y}`.
The measure `E_{a, x, y}` is defined via the Riesz-Markov-Kakutani theorem from the linear functional `φ_{x,y} : g ↦ ⟪x, g(a) y⟫`.
The dependence on `y` in `φ_{x,y}` is linear: `φ_{x, c • y} (g) = ⟪x, g(a) (c • y)⟫ = c ⟪x, g(a) y⟫ = c • φ_{x,y} (g)`.
The map from functionals to measures (inverse of Riesz map) is linear.
Thus `E_{a, x, c • y} = c • E_{a, x, y}`.
The integral is linear in the measure: `∫ f d(c • μ) = c ∫ f dμ`.

